properties.name: Bassett St. - 1st Apartment
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman First apartment. Lived there sophomore year with Erica and three other girls. It had a turret and a wraparound 3-season porch.

properties.name: Big Foot High School
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman That belligerent dwarf Hinske is the principal now, so God knows what it\'s like being a Big Foot student these days, but I have to say that I had a good enough time there...

properties.name: Chadbourne Honors Dorm
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman What would have been the nerd dorm, I suppose, if it weren\'t also an amazing location that everybody wanted. Freshman year, 6th floor maybe (hard to remember).

properties.name: Golden Years
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman My first job, working in the kitchen from sophomore year of high school through the summer between freshman and sophomore year of college.

properties.name: Hanny's Restaurant
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman  Cups of coffee for a buck, cigarettes, and games of napkins... Unfortunately, closed for a couple years now (R.I.P.).

properties.name: Jenifer St. Apartment
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman Lived there senior year with Erica, Ryan, and Kelli. Right across the street from the Co-op and Star Liquor. Nice.

properties.name: Jurg's Greenhouse
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman Another early job of mine, stocking impatiens, geraniums, and begonias and slinging bags of mulch. I have vivid memories of eating hot italian beef out of a crock pot for lunch, with enough hot giardiniera to make you sweat even if you weren\'t in a greenhouse.

properties.name: Römerlager
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman My Studentenwohnheim in Bonn. A classic modernist German high-rise dorm. I had a view of the Rheinfluß for a year!

properties.name: The Farm
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman Where my Mom and her brothers and sisters grew up. My twin brother and I spent a lot of time growing up there as well. My Aunt Mary lives in the house now, with Uncle Paul in the house to the north, and Uncle Ted in the house to the south.

properties.name: The Square
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman Upon which we are "The Friendly Little Village." The sculpture of the geese was made by my Grandpa Rohner. It used to be more centrally located in the square, but then some guy who was leading the police in a high-speed chase came down Hwy 14, couldn\'t make the turns around the square, and ended up going right through it instead and smashing into the piece. It\'s fixed now, of course, and in the southwest corner of the park. Also noteworthy here: Corn and Brat Fest!

properties.name: The Superman Tower
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman The Superman Tower, so named because when we used to see it from our house as kids, we believed it was Superman\'s home base. In later years we always talked about climbing it some night. I\'d say Josh and I might still, but I guess even if my falling to my death wouldn\'t be a big deal, he\'s got two kids now. Oh well, I haven\'t given up on the idea yet... Picture is from just west of corner of State Line and Alden, looking south.

properties.name: Walworth Elementary
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman When I think of grade school, I think of the top of the stairwell near Mr. Schroeder\'s and Mrs. Wessels\'s rooms. And back even further, the smell of pencil boxes and the book fair, and getting excited about rain-day recess.

properties.name: Where I Grew Up
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman W5501 Lakeville Rd. Walworth, WI 53184Rural area outside the "Friendly Little Village on the Square."

properties.name: Where I grew up.
properties.description: Posted by Quinngorman Just outside "The Friendly Village on the Square." Best place anyone could ever hope to grow up.
